INSERT INTO `cruise` (`id`, `name`, `city_id`, `description`, `image`, `review`, `review_image`, `location`, `location_image`, `rooms`, `rooms_image`, `dining`, `dining_image`, `leisure`, `leisure_image`, `ordering`, `meta_title`, `meta_keyword`, `meta_description`, `url`) VALUES
(1, 'AQUA MEKONG', 1, '<p>The brand new Aqua Mekong is poised to set new standards for Mekong river cruising. With 20 Design Suites explore the Mekong River in style between Cambodia and Vietnam. Private skiffs allow guests to get closer to the river during shore excursions off the vessel.&nbsp;</p>', 'Aqua_Mekong_New_Mekong_Cruise.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">A Touch of Asia have yet to inspect the Aqua Mekong but expectations are high based on the sister boats that sail on the Amazon. This is expected to be a floating 5 star boutique vessel with carefully crafted excursions.&nbsp;</p>', '', '<p>3 night options from Phnom Penh to Saigon or Phnom Penh to Siem Reap</p>\n<p>4 night options from Siem Reap to Phnom Penh or Saigon to Phnom Penh</p>\n<p>7 night options from Siem Reap to Saigon or vice versa.</p>\n<p>Itineraries vary according to high or low water levels.</p>', 'Luxury_Boutique_Cruise_Mekong.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">20 Design Suites are generous at 30m&sup2; and eight also have balconies. All offer floor to ceiling panoramic windows allowing guests to open all the way and enjoy the fresh air whilst gazing upon the river from their king size bed that can be converted into two twin beds. A bathroom with rainforest shower compliments the facilities befitting of a 5 star hotel.</p>', 'Deluxe_Cabin_Suites.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Menus have been designed by Executive Chef, David Thompson, the star behind London&rsquo;s Michelin star, Nahm. Combining the culinary traditions of Mekong River cultures with the freshest ingredients like Khmer Kampot pepper, Mekong River prawns, and for the most intrepid guests, grilled Battambang snake, life on board will be an amazing culinary adventure.&nbsp;</p>', 'Culinary_Mekong_delights.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Relax with some traditional therapy in the two specially designed spa rooms, cool down in the shaded plunge pool on the observation deck or shop in the cruise boutique. Other facilities include a screening room, a library/games room with the Mekong''s only football table and a top deck gym overlooking the river.&nbsp;</p>', 'Bar_Lounge_Luxury_Cruise.jpg', 1, 'Aqua Cruises in Cambodia : A touch of Asia ', 'cruises on tonle sap, cruises in cambodia', 'Cruises and voyage on the rivers of Cambodia. Luxury sojourn with all inclusive', 'aqua-cruises-in-cambodia-by-touchofasia-travel'),
(2, 'JAYAVARMAN', 1, '<p class="MsoNormal">With just 27 cabins, the Jayavarman sails between Cambodia and Vietnam and combines the art deco charm of 1930&rsquo;s France with the romance of Indochine. With three and half decks the spacious vessel offers the chance to experience the river in the same way as the earliest explorers. &nbsp;</p>', 'Jayavarman_Luxury_Cruise.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">The Jayavarman offers the chance to experience river cruising at its best with supremely comfortable cabins and great service on board. The boat feels like a 5 star floating hotel and does not disappoint. Unlike its sister boat (Jahan) the Jayavarman has more Indochine elegance.</p>', '', '<p>3 night options from Phnom Penh to Saigon or vice versa (Pearl of the Orient)</p>\n<p>3 night option from Siem Reap to Phnom Penh (Serenity Cruise)</p>\n<p>4 night options from Siem Reap to Phnom Penh or vice versa (Serenity Cruise)</p>\n<p>7 night options from Siem Reap to Saigon or vice versa (Lost Civilization)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal">Itineraries vary according to high or low water levels.</p>', 'Mekong_Cruise_Sundeck.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">14 Superior Cabins located on the Main Deck offer 21m&sup2;space. 11 Deluxe Cabins on the Upper Deck offer more space at 30m&sup2;. 2 elegant Signature Cabins are also available. All cabins on the Jayavarman have their own private balcony.</p>', 'Stylish_Mekong_Cabin.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Guests can enjoy dining in the elegant Indochine Dining Hall, mingle in the Club 1930 Bar can admire Khmer artefacts in the Henry Mouhot Lounge. Breakfast is buffet style with noodles and eggs a la carte. At other mealtimes the cuisine is East meets West with set menus to meet different tastes.&nbsp;</p>', 'Gourmet_Dining.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Besides enjoying art in the lounge guests can take advantage of some spa treatment at the Apsara Beauty &amp; Wellness Spa, watch the river scenery from the sunbed or cool down in the Jacuzzi on the sundeck. An on-board boutique sells souvenirs from the region.</p>', 'Apsara_Spa_on_cruise.jpg', 3, 'Jayavarman cruises on the Mekong rivers', 'jayavarman cruises, boat cruises in asia', 'Go back in time, in the charming 1930''s era to cruise from Saigon to Siem Reap, on a beautiful art-deco vessel', 'jayavarman-boat-cruise-in-south-east-asia'),
(3, 'JAHAN', 1, '<p class="MsoNormal">With just 26 cabins, the Jahan is considered the most romantic of cruise vessels with an elegant design inspired by an Indian emperor. Sailing the same routes between Cambodia and Vietnam as the sister Jayavarman cruise, a few days or a week on board is the ideal way to explore the Indochine waterways.</p>', 'Elegant_Jahan_Mekong_Cruise.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">There is little to separate the Jahan and Jayavarman cruises in quality &ndash; not surprising as they have the same owners. The main differences are an Indian inspired design on the Jahan, more spacious entry level cabins and the inclusion of a swimming pool. The last part might be the clincher as cooling down in the river is not an option&hellip;</p>', '', '<p>3 night options from Phnom Penh to Saigon or vice versa (Pearl of the Orient)</p>\n<p>3 night option from Siem Reap to Phnom Penh (Serenity Cruise)</p>\n<p>4 night options from Siem Reap to Phnom Penh or vice versa (Serenity Cruise)</p>\n<p>7 night options from Siem Reap to Saigon or vice versa (Lost Civilization)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal">Itineraries vary according to high or low water levels.</p>', 'Pool_Deck_Jahan.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">12 Superior cabins are located on the Main Deck and 8 Deluxe cabins on the Upper Deck. 4 Signature Suites, 1 Taj Suite &amp; 1 Lord Byrons Suite offer some intriguing upgrade options. All cabins come with their own private balcony.</p>', 'Spacious_Jahan_Superior_Cabin.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Next to the bar on the Terrace Deck, the Viceroy Dining Hall is spread out on the top of the ship where you can enjoy al-fresco dining. Savour lavish buffet breakfasts complete with juices and freshly brewed tea and coffee. Expect to relish exotic fruits, organic vegetables, fish and prawns as you cruise. The East India Club funnel bar is the place to enjoy a morning coffee or a pre-dinner cocktail.</p>', 'Dining_Mekong_Observatory.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Soak up the atmosphere at the East India Club; soak in the Jacuzzi on the Pool Deck; relax in the Observatory Lounge; or enjoy a pampering massage in the Apsara Spa. With three decks, this vessel offers all the amenities of a fine resort, including a fitness centre and steam rooms.&nbsp;</p>', 'Apsara_Spa_Jahan_Cruise.jpg', 4, 'Jahan cruises from Cambodia to Vietnam', 'jahan cruises, boat ride from cambodia to vietnam', 'This elegant Indian-empire inspired vessel is considered the most romantic cruise trip in the south east asian region. Book today', 'jahan-cruises-vietnam-cambodia-trip'),
(4, 'TOUM TIOU I', 1, '<p>Spend a week on board Toum Tiou I (also called Toum Teav) to combine the bustling cities of Saigon and Phnom Penh with a Mekong River cruise. With just 10 cabins this small and personal cruise offers longer cruising and smaller destinations to be visited in comparison to the larger vessels.</p>', 'Quality_Mekong_Cruise.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">A small and intimate boat in which to enjoy river cruising. Considered as a 4 star boat this is one of our favourites and comes from the longest established cruising company on the Mekong. An advantage of the smaller vessel is the Toum Tiou can get closer to Siem Reap and sail all the way to Saigon &ndash; the larger vessels cannot do this and road transfers are required.</p>', '', '<p>7 night options from Siem Reap to Saigon or vice versa.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Toum Tiou I also occasionally sails the shorter stretch from Phnom Penh to Siem Reap or vice versa which is a 2 night option.</p>', 'Idyllic_Mekong_Life.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Toum Tiou has 10 cosy double cabins; each with a private lounge area, air conditioning, hi-fi system, and en suite bathroom with hot/cold private shower. Cabins are located on the Main or Upper Deck.&nbsp;</p>', 'Twin_Cabin.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Cuisine on board is a mixture of East meets West in the Upper Deck restaurant. A semi-buffet breakfast and lunch is followed by themed dinner. Tea, coffee and drinking water are complimentary. An extensive wine list with premium wines and liquors is also available.</p>', 'Delicious_Food_on_Board.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">A lounge area offers the chance to unwind and enjoy evening lectures. One of the advantages of the Toum Tiou I is that with the boat&rsquo;s low draft it allows access to the remotest of villages and to gently hug the river line, affording passengers priceless views of people, flora and fauna.</p>', 'Relax_on_the_sundeck.jpg', 5, 'Tom Toui 1 - Cruises', 'mekong cruises, river cruises', 'Discover the Mekong at the soft pace of the cruise ship. relax and contemplate the Kingdom from the sundeck', 'mekong-river-cruises-tom-toui'),
(5, 'TOUM TIOU II', 1, '<p class="MsoNormal">Toum Tiou II, naturally a sister of Toum Tiou I, offers a similar river cruise, albeit with 14 cabins. The low draft of the vessels means smaller villages and greater distance can be cruised when comparing to the larger boats on a similar route.</p>', '4_Star_Mekong_Cruise.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">We like Toum Tiou II as it means a more personal experience, getting closer to the river bank and with the backup of a long established cruising company to ensure the most comfortable services on and off board. Toum Tiou II offers some different cruise durations in case guests do not have the time for the full week programme.</p>', '', '<p>7 night options from Siem Reap to Saigon or vice versa.</p>\n<p>2 night options from Siem Reap to Phnom Penh or vice versa.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;At the end of March and in April a 6 night option from Phnom Penh to Saigon (and vice versa) is also offered.&nbsp;</p>', 'Serene_Mekong_Landscapes.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">The Toum Tiou II cabins offers a private lounge area, air conditioning, hi-fi system, and on-suite bathroom with hot/cold private shower and complimentary tea and coffee. The 14 cozy cabins are fitted to the highest specifications with noble wood finishes in an elegant colonial style. Cabins are locally on the Main and Upper Decks.</p>', 'Comfortable_Twin_Cabin.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal">Cuisine on board is a mixture of East meets West in the Upper Deck restaurant. A semi-buffet breakfast and lunch is followed by themed dinner. Tea, coffee and drinking water are complimentary. An extensive wine list with premium wines and liquors is also available.</p>', 'Cuisine_on_the_cruise.jpg', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">Enjoy educational lectures on board, relax in the library or use the free WiFi on board. Of course enjoying the majestic riverine scenery is likely to take up most of your time.</p>', 'Sundeck_Toum_Tiou.jpg', 2, 'Luxury cruises on the mekong river', 'cruises, mekong', 'There are no better way to visit and discover a country than at the pace of a ship, gently cruising the river', 'cruises-over-the-mekong-tom-tiou');

