; carvings, all of which are different. The late afternoon light provides the best opportunity to observe and photograph the Apsaras.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Enjoy sunset at Angkor Wat with a cold coconut juice to cool down after your exciting exploration.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">On the way back to your hotel stop at a real, authentic Night Market. See the various deep-fried insects on sale, amongst grilled frogs, grilled fish and tapioca desserts.</span></p>', 'culture-cuisine-d1.jpg'),
(1983, 11, '4: SIEM REAP ', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="EN-US">A very special morning awaits you today. Leave the hotel at around 5am to experience sunrise at a choice of Pre Rup Temple or the Sra Srang pool.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Continue to traditional Khmer wooden house is the setting for an energizing noodle breakfast, a very popular Khmer breakfast dish.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Following your hearty breakfast continue to Ta Prohm, also known as the ''Tomb Raider'' temple.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">In the early evening enjoy a pre-dinner aperitif of an infused rice wine called &lsquo;Sombai&rsquo; (meaning &lsquo;some rice please&rsquo; in the Khmer language). The Sombai workshop is located in a charming wooden house a few minutes&rsquo; drive from Siem Reap town. Beautifully hand-painted bottles make for an interesting souvenir.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Continue for dinner at one of Siem Reap&rsquo;s most popular restaurants serving </span><span lang="EN-US">traditional </span><span lang="EN-US">Khmer food, in a lush contemporary setting.&nbsp;</span></p>', 'culture-cuisine-d4.jpg');
