 the Baphoun, Terrace of the Elephants and Terrace of the Leper King.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Around lunchtime return to your hotel where the afternoon is free for you to either explore the pleasant town of Siem Reap on your own accord or relax at&nbsp; your hotel.</p>\n<p>This evening enjoy a Welcome Dinner whilst watching a show of Apsara dancing, first performed in the court of kings at Angkor.</p>\n<p>A set menu of Khmer cuisine will be served as you enjoy the show.</p>', 'cambodia-cuisine-d2.jpg');
