e 3 Accent 5"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="49" Name="List Table 4 Accent 5"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="50" Name="List Table 5 Dark Accent 5"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="51"\n   Name="List Table 6 Colorful Accent 5"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="52"\n   Name="List Table 7 Colorful Accent 5"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="46"\n   Name="List Table 1 Light Accent 6"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="47" Name="List Table 2 Accent 6"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="48" Name="List Table 3 Accent 6"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="49" Name="List Table 4 Accent 6"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="50" Name="List Table 5 Dark Accent 6"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="51"\n   Name="List Table 6 Colorful Accent 6"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="52"\n   Name="List Table 7 Colorful Accent 6"/>\n </w:LatentStyles>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\n<style>\n /* Style Definitions */\n table.MsoNormalTable\n	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\n	mso-style-priority:99;\n	mso-style-parent:"";\n	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\n	mso-para-margin:0in;\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\n	font-size:12.0pt;\n	font-family:"Cambria","serif";\n	mso-ascii-font-family:Cambria;\n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Cambria;\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\n	mso-bidi-language:AR-SA;}\n</style>\n<![endif]--></p>\n<p>In the morning travel to the countryside a short distance outside of Siem Reap town. Transfer 10 minutes out of town by remork to a local village where you will try a hands-on cookery class&nbsp;<span lang="EN-US">(class shared with other participants).</span>&nbsp;Khmer cuisine is not as well-known as that from Vietnam or Thailand though is equally as good. Fresh, seasonal fruits, vegetables and spice combine to make dishes less spicy than countries such as Laos or Thailand but rich in taste.</p>\n<p>After an introduction to your chef for the morning it is time to take a walk through the village to visit a local family and see many of the ingredients being grown. Return to a purpose built bamboo pavilion where you will learn about Khmer cuisine as you cook at your individual work station surrounded by coconut and bamboo trees. A 3 course meal is prepared as part of the interactive lesson.</p>\n<p>Later relax at a different pavilion perched over a fish pond as you enjoy your own cooking.</p>\n<p>Return to the hotel after lunch by remork where your afternoon is free.</p>\n<p>In the evening enjoy some modern Khmer theatre at a performance of Phare, the Cambodian Circus by professional artists from Phare Ponleu Selpak. Originally a project set up in refugee camps as a way to encourage young people to express themselves using art, the Phare circus is slowly becoming a worldwide name. Tours have visited France, Germany and the UK already. Enjoy an hour long show which is a great, positive example of modern Cambodia and mixes theatre, dance, music, juggling and contortion.</p>\n<p>The rest of the evening is free for you to take dinner on your own or return to the hotel.</p>', 'cambodia-cuisine-d3.jpg'),
(2022, 13, '1: PHNOM PENH - KEP ', '<p><span lang="EN-US">This morning you will be collected at your Phnom Penh hotel (or airport). With your guide it is time to head south with a couple of stops on the way to Kep (transfer time 4&frac12;-5hrs including stops). </span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Stop at Tonle Bati to see a very small but pretty temple called Ta Prohm. A little further along the highway stop at another temple from the Angkorian era, Phnom Chisor. Over 400 steps lead up the hillside to the temple which provides an excellent panoramic view of the countryside.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Arrive in Kep to check into Knai Bang Chatt in the early afternoon. Take your time to settle in to your home for the next 4 nights.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Meal included: </span><span lang="EN-US">None&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Accommodation at:</span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US">Knai Bang Chatt, Kep</span></p>', 'coastal-cuisine-d1.jpg'),
(2023, 13, '2: KEP', '<p><span lang="EN-US">This morning get acquainted with Khmer coastal cuisine by way of a half day cooking class at Knai Bang Chatt. The course starts with a visit to the famous Crab Market where the chef will introduce and explain the various spices and local produce on offer. Once back at the resort, you will have the chance to prepare and enjoy 3-4 traditional Cambodian dishes. </span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">The afternoon is free at leisure. Knai Bang Chatt offers plenty of leisure activities including mountain bikes for hire, tuk tuk tours or sailing courses. You can also take the chance to explore the local scenery/</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Meal included: </span><span lang="EN-US">Breakfast/Lunch at cookery class</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Acommodation at:</span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;Knai Bang Chatt, Kep</span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: ''Comic Sans MS'';">&nbsp;</span></p>', 'coastal-cuisine-d2.jpg'),
(2024, 13, '3: KEP', '<p><span lang="EN-US">This morning get closer to the local culture and way of life as you learn to fish like the locals. Drive out of Kep to a fishing village. Board a local fishing boat and pass through mangrove forests and learn several traditional fishing techniques. With luck, you may find that you have a selection of fish, shrimp, and crab to bring back.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Meal included: </span><span lang="EN-US">Breakfast/Picnic Lunch</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Accommodation at:</span><span lang="EN-US"> Knai Bang Chatt, Kep</span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: ''Comic Sans MS'';">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>', 'coastal-cuisine-d3.jpg');
