f the most interesting cities in Asia.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">In the afternoon visit the Toul Sleng Genocide Museum. During the Pol Pot regime, Toul Sleng, formerly a high school was converted to a detention centre known as S21. During the Khmer Rouge years, thousands of Cambodians were tortured and imprisoned in detention centres around the country. &nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Finish the afternoon with a local shopping experience at Toul Tom Pong Market (also the Russian Market).</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">This evening dine at a non-profit restaurant run by which has worked to build the futures of former street children and marginalized young people in Phnom Penh since 1994. Your visit helps sustain the project and importantly keeps the staff and their trainers away from the street and in gainful employment.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Meal included:&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US">Dinner&nbsp; </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="EN-US">Accommodation at:</span><span lang="EN-US"> Selected hotel, Phnom Penh</span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp; &nbsp; </span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: ''Garamond'',''serif'';">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>', 'phnom-penh-cuisine-d1.jpg'),
(1914, 15, '1: ARRIVAL PHNOM PENH', '<p><span lang="EN-US">Upon arrival at Phnom Penh airport you will be met by our local English speaking Tour Guide and transferred to your hotel to check in. </span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Phnom Penh was known as the &lsquo;Pearl of Asia&rsquo; and like much of Cambodia was a vibrant and culturally developed city until the 1960&rsquo;s. Suffering at the hands of the Khmer Rouge the city was once evacuated by Pol Pot&rsquo;s army and became a ghost town. Today&rsquo;s Cambodia is ever changing and one of the most interesting cities in Asia.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">In the evening head off for dinner at one of Cambodia&rsquo;s most famous restaurants and the best address in Phnom Penh to try Khmer cuisine.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Meal included: </span><span lang="EN-US">Dinner&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="EN-US">Accommodation at:</span><span lang="EN-US"> Selected hotel, Phnom Penh</span></p>', '48hours-phnompenh-d1.jpg');
