he Royal Palace made up from a number of structures within a pagoda-style compound one of which is The Silver Pagoda. &nbsp;Continue to visit the National Museum, a Khmer temple inspired building that houses the world&rsquo;s largest collection of Khmer art sculptures, ceramics and bronzes from different periods of Cambodian history.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Enjoy some authentic Khmer cooking a venue with ambience. The restaurant is a former typical house from the protectorate period where today, delicious classical home style Cambodian cuisine is served.</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">After transfer to the airport for your departure flight. &lsquo;Chum reap lear&rsquo; and goodbye to the Kingdom of Wonder</span></p>\n<p><span lang="EN-US">Meal included: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang="EN-US">Breakfast/Lunch</span><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: ''Comic Sans MS''; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;</span></p>', '48hours-phnompenh-d3.jpg');
